mng: classifier for years (of age), year, year (of crop harvests)
variant of 歲|岁[sui4], year, years old

exm.mng: one full year (e.g. on child's first birthday)
Long live (the king, the revolution etc)!, Your Majesty, His Majesty
money given to children as new year present
Taisu, God of the year, archaic name for the planet Jupiter 木星[Mù Xīng], nickname for sb who is the most powerful in an area
some years, How many years?, How old are you? (familiar, or to child, equivalent to 多大 for older person)
